coordinate_descent_0 <- function(g, alpha_choice = 1, max_its = 100, w0, tol = 10^-5) {
  #coordinate descent function for a local minimum for a two dimensional input
  #Args:
  #g: an objective function
  #alpha_choice: if "diminishing", use diminishing steplength, if numerical, use that value as a fixed steplength
  #max_its: maximum number of iterations
  #w0: initial weight value (two-dimensional)
  #tol: the tolerance for the stop criteria
  #Return:
  #list containing the weight histories and the cost histories by the algorithm
  
  weight_history = matrix(w0)      
  cost_history = g(w0)           
  alpha = 0
  w = w0
  
  for (i in 1:max_its) {
    if (alpha_choice == 'diminishing') {
      alpha = 1/i
    } else {
      alpha = alpha_choice
    }
    
    # we will grab a random unit direction in R2 space by using cosine and sine:
    angle <- runif(1, min = 0, max = 2*pi)
    direction <- rbind(cos(angle), sin(angle))
    
    w_test_1 <- w + alpha*direction
    w_test_2 <- w - alpha*direction
    g_vals <- c(g(w_test_1), g(w_test_2))
    
    index <- which.min(g_vals)
    if (index == 1) {
      if (g(w_test_1) < g(w)) {
        w <- w + alpha*direction
      } 
    } else {
      if (g(w_test_2) < g(w)) {
        w <- w - alpha*direction
      }
    }
    
    if (abs(g(w) - cost_history[i]) <= tol) {
      break
    }
    
    weight_history <- cbind(weight_history, w)
    cost_history <- c(cost_history, g(w))
  }
  
  list(weights = weight_history, costs = cost_history)
}

a)

gd <- function(g, g_prime, alpha_choice = 1, max_its = 100, w0, tol = 10^-5, normalized = 0, momentum = F) {
  #gradient descent function for a local minimum
  #Args:
  #g: an objective function
  #g_prime: the corresponding gradient
  #alpha_choice: if "diminishing", use diminishing steplength, if numerical, use that value as a fixed steplength
  #max_its: maximum number of iterations
  #w0: initial weight value (two-dimensional)
  #tol: the tolerance for the stop criteria
  #normalized: (1: full normalized; 0: unnormalized; -1: component-wise normalized)
  #momentum: can perform momentum-accelerated gradient descent
  #Return:
  #list containing the weight histories and the cost histories by the algorithm
  weight_history = matrix(w0)      
  cost_history = g(w0)           
  alpha = 0
  beta = 0.1
  w = w0
  
  for (i in 1:max_its) {
    
    if (alpha_choice == 'diminishing') {
      alpha = 1/i
    } else {
      alpha = alpha_choice
    }
  
    if (normalized == 0) {
      direction <- -g_prime(w)
    }
    if (normalized == 1) {
      direction <- -g_prime(w)
      direction <- direction / norm(direction)
    }
    if (normalized == -1) {
      direction <- -g_prime(w)
      direction <- sign(direction)
    }
    if (momentum) {
      if (i == 1){
        direction <- -g_prime(w0)
      } 
      else {
        direction <- beta * oldDirection + (1-beta) * direction
      }
      
      oldDirection <- direction
    }
  
    w <- w + alpha * direction
    weight_history <- cbind(weight_history, w)
    cost_history <- c(cost_history, g(w))
    
    # stop criteria
    if (abs(g(w) - cost_history[i]) <= tol) {
      break
    }
  }
  list(weights = weight_history, costs = cost_history)
}
